<br>
Back on Guinevere though where I play a 50 hero and 47 champ, meeting savages are nasty affairs. I have seen them running through large battles dropping people left and right dishing out damage that makes me drool. Even 1 on 1 a half wounded savage has taken me out! <br>
<br>
I am wondering now, if the savage might be the number one predator on the food chain. Granted I havent seen a savage and an assasin fight, but if they can do the kind of damage that I have seen, perhaps even assasins leave them alone.<br>
<br>
Comments? Or am I way out in left feild? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iria2@lighttanksofdaoc>iria2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(7/30/03 3:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Food Chain</span><hr size=1> I'd say so.  I play Alb on Lancelot and i dont think ive run into a group in the past couple of months that didnt have at least one savage in it.  One on One they also molest me, but for some reason people decide not to buff my merc alot <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
  Since savages do lack the hitpoints of a pure tank however, I hear that slam can really screw them over, especially against classes like the reaver who are also positional based and have high dmg output, especially lev.<br>
<br>
But anyhow, I'm just wondering if savages can still get their multi-hit styles off even if they dont meet the prerequisite of the previous chain style, or perform the style correctly.  Thats probably the only big issue i have with them though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=neplak>Neplak</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.nep.nu/nep/eqdocs/sweden.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(8/7/03 2:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=56.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://nep.nu/nep/nepmini.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Food Chain</span><hr size=1> Quote -- Since savages do lack the hitpoints of a pure tank however<br>
